content: On September 16, 1993, the Atlanta Braves secured their fifth consecutive National League West title, defeating the Philadelphia Phillies 7-6 in a thrilling game at Veterans Stadium. The victory was highlighted by a key three-run homer by Fred McGriff, which helped solidify the Braves' dominance in the division during the early 1990s. This win was part of a remarkable season that would eventually lead the Braves to the World Series.
